This is a network of interactions among students living in a fraternity at a West Virginia college. An observer recorded the number of times a pair of subjects were seen in conversation by walking through the public areas of the building every fifteen minutes, 21 hours a day, for five days.

This network records amateur HAM radio calls made over a one-month period, as monitored by a voice-activated recording device.

This network records amateur HAM radio operators perceptions of how frequently they talked to other operators, judged retrospectively at the end of the one-month sampling period. A value of 0 meaning no interaction up to a maximum of 9.

This network includes the observed frequency of interactions in a small business office. Observations were made as the observer patrolled a fixed route through the office every fifteen minutes during two four-day periods.

This network includes rankings of interaction frequency as recalled by the employees in a small business office over the two-week period. The rankings go from 1 for the most frequent to 39 for the least frequent.
This network concerns  frequency record of interactions, made by an observer every half-hour during one five-day work week in a technical research group at a West Virginia university.

This network concerns the personal rankings of the remembered frequency of interactions in one five-day work week in a technical research group at a West Virginia university. The rankings go from 1 for the most frequent up to 36 for the least frequent.
